SIMPLE: malignancy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malignancy
<hw>Ma*lig"nan*cy</hw> ,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Malignant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state or quality of being malignant; extreme malevolence;
bitter enmity; malice; disposition toward evil; intense ill will;
<as>as, <ex>malignancy</ex> of heart</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unfavorableness; evil nature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>malignancy</qex> of my fate might perhaps distemner
yours.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Virulence; tendency to a fatal
issue; <as>as, the <ex>malignancy</ex> of an ulcer or of a
fever</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
cancerous tumor that is spreading beyond the point of origin.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> malignant tumor, malignant neoplasm, metastatic
tumor.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The state of being a malignant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>malignant</ent>⟦br⟧
